"{\"uid\": \"capitalethiopia.com-2024-06-24-yomif-prevails-over-berihu-in-ethiopian-olympic-10000m-trials\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Yomif Kejelcha took a thrilling narrow win at the Ethiopian 10,000m Olympic trials held in Nerja, Spain.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 14, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yomif_Kejelcha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yomif Kejelcha\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yomif_Kejelcha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yomif_Kejelcha\"}, {\"begin\": 50, \"end\": 59, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9919556025648097, \"rank\": 0.008109634557932541, \"text\": \"Ethiopian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 91, \"end\": 96, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nerja\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nerja\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nerja\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nerja\"}, {\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9870842725452381, \"rank\": 0.013083757500134284, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 26-year-old smashed his lifetime best by 18 seconds to clock a world-leading 26:31.01 after an incredibly tight sprint with Berihu Aregawi, who also improved his career best to 26:31.13.\", \"from\": 106, \"to\": 296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 234, \"end\": 248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berihu_Aregawi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Berihu Aregawi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berihu_Aregawi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berihu_Aregawi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The third spot on Ethiopia's team for Paris went to Olympic champion Selemon Barega, who was timed at 26:34.93.\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 315, \"end\": 323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999974989, \"rank\": 2.464820280002136e-12, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 335, \"end\": 340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999371375877, \"rank\": 6.286244383813364e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 366, \"end\": 380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selemon_Barega\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Selemon Barega\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selemon_Barega\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selemon_Barega\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one of the highest quality 10,000m races ever, four men finished inside 26:40 and six men finished inside 26:50 for the first time.\", \"from\": 410, \"to\": 544, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"17-year-old Biniam Mehary placed fourth in a world U20 record of 26:37.93, taking four seconds off the previous mark set 19 years ago by the late Samuel Wanjiru.\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 596, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0358421941399763e-17, \"text\": \"U20\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 698, \"end\": 705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evelyn_Wanjiru\", \"score\": 0.999999998254907, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wanjiru\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evelyn_Wanjiru\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evelyn_Wanjiru\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On a mild (21C), windless night and in a race with good pacemaking, Aregawi, Kejelcha, Barega, and Mehari went through the halfway mark in 13:17.\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 807, \"end\": 813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\", \"score\": 0.9810060459411328, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mehari\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One kilometer later, the last pacemaker dropped out of the race, and from then on the world 5km record-holder Aregawi pushed hard, trying to leave his rivals behind, but only the young Mehari lost ground in the ninth kilometer.\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1039, \"end\": 1045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\", \"score\": 0.9810060459411328, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mehari\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Citro\\u00ebn_M\\u00e9hari\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shortly after reaching the bell, Barega began to fade, and the event became a two-way showdown between Aregawi and Kejelcha.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1207, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latter tried to overtake his compatriot on the final bend, but Aregawi managed to hold off his first attack; Kejelcha never surrendered, and finally, he edged ahead of Aregawi just 30 meters before the finish line.\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the women's race, Fotyen Tesfay took an impressive victory in 29:47.71, putting her just outside the top 10 on the world all-time list.\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1566, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"2023 world cross-country silver medalist Tsigie Gebreselama was second in 29:49:33, ahead of world bronze medalist Ejgayehu Taye (29:50:52), who also set a lifetime best.\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1608, \"end\": 1626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsigie_Gebreselama\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tsigie Gebreselama\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsigie_Gebreselama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsigie_Gebreselama\"}, {\"begin\": 1682, \"end\": 1695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ejgayehu_Taye\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ejgayehu Taye\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ejgayehu_Taye\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ejgayehu_Taye\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hot this week  Popular Categories  Capital is the longest-established private English newspaper in Ethiopia  Contact us:info@capitalethiopia.com  \\u00a9 Newspaper WordPress Theme by TagDiv\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1922, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1838, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999974989, \"rank\": 2.464820280002136e-12, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}]}"